From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 7 Jul 2026 14:15:01 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/7] Fix trading pipeline flow: wire Scanner into Decision
 Score and route Chief Decision through Risk

- scoring/engine.py: subscribe to scanner_match events so scanner opportunities
  trigger a decision score evaluation, not just candle-driven market analysis.
- agents/chief_decision_agent.py: approved decisions now publish order_request
  (consumed by RiskAgent) instead of order_approved directly, so orders pass
  through the dedicated Risk Agent before reaching Execution as intended by the
  Market Feed -> Scanner -> Decision Score -> Chief Decision -> Risk -> Execution
  -> Paper Broker -> Trade Saved -> Dashboard pipeline.
- Fix AttributeError crash (self.name -> self.agent_name) and missing required
  AgentResultModel fields (reason, processing_time) in ChiefDecisionAgent.analyze,
  which previously crashed the agent after every decision.
- Add integration tests covering the scanner-to-score and chief-decision-to-risk
  wiring.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 5 <noreply@anthropic.com>
